## 5.4  configuration/variables.tf

The Terraform variable holding the database admin password was renamed from postgres_admin_password to cosmosdb_postgres_password. The description was updated to reference Cosmos DB for PostgreSQL. No default value or sensitivity setting was changed.

  # Before

  variable "postgres_admin_password" {

    description = "Admin password for the PostgreSQL Flexible Server..."

    type        = string

    default     = ""

    sensitive   = true

  }

  # After

  variable "cosmosdb_postgres_password" {

    description = "Admin password for the Azure Cosmos DB for PostgreSQL cluster..."

    type        = string

    default     = ""

    sensitive   = true

  }

## 5.5  configuration/main.tf

The reference to the renamed Terraform variable was updated in the locals block that injects DB_PASSWORD as a Container App secret.

  # Before

  var.postgres_admin_password != "" ? { DB_PASSWORD = var.postgres_admin_password } : {},

  # After

  var.cosmosdb_postgres_password != "" ? { DB_PASSWORD = var.cosmosdb_postgres_password } : {},

The inline comment above this expression was updated to describe Cosmos DB for PostgreSQL instead of Azure PostgreSQL Flexible Server.

## 5.6  .github/workflows/deploy.yaml

The Terraform plan step passes the database password from a GitHub environment secret into a Terraform variable. The variable name argument was updated to match the renamed variable. The GitHub secret itself (POSTGRES_ADMIN_PASSWORD) is unchanged — no repository admin action is required.

  # Before

  -var="postgres_admin_password=${{ secrets.POSTGRES_ADMIN_PASSWORD }}"

  # After

  -var="cosmosdb_postgres_password=${{ secrets.POSTGRES_ADMIN_PASSWORD }}"

## 5.7  app/optimizer/models.py

The module-level docstring that documents the minimum DATABASES settings.py configuration was updated to reflect Cosmos DB for PostgreSQL as the backend, show the correct host format, and use the correct default user and database name.

